
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `fc-scan` baraye gardesh dar file-ha va peyda kardan font-ha estefade mishavad.  In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad font-haye mojood ra dar system-e khod peyda konid va etela'ati darbareye anha kasb konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `fc-scan --format="%{family}\n"` --> 🖋️ Namayesh esm-e family-e font-ha faghat.
    🔹 `fc-scan /path/be/pooshe/font-ha` --> 📁 Scan kardan yek pooshe-ye moshakhas baraye font-ha.
    🔹 `fc-scan --verbose` --> 🗣️ Namayesh etela'at bishtar darbareye font-ha (path, features, va...).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ fc-scan

    🔹 List kardan hameye font-haye system ba etela'at-e default.

    $ fc-scan /usr/share/fonts

    🔹 Scan kardan poosheye `/usr/share/fonts` baraye font-ha.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ fc-scan | grep "Arial"

    🔹 Peyda kardan font-haye Arial dar khorooji `fc-scan`.  Az `grep` baraye filter kardan natije estefade shodeh.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `fc-scan` command is used to scan files and locate fonts.  This tool helps you find the available fonts on your system and gather information about them.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `fc-scan --format="%{family}\n"` --> 🖋️ Display only the font family names.
    🔹 `fc-scan /path/to/fonts/directory` --> 📁 Scan a specific directory for fonts.
    🔹 `fc-scan --verbose` --> 🗣️ Display more detailed information about the fonts (path, features, etc.).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ fc-scan

    🔹 List all fonts in the system with default information.

    $ fc-scan /usr/share/fonts

    🔹 Scan the `/usr/share/fonts` directory for fonts.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ fc-scan | grep "Arial"

    🔹 Find Arial fonts in the `fc-scan` output.  `grep` is used to filter the result.
